Most (all?) of cons are related to management.
- Strong opposition to change of any kind;
- Most managers and up have a nurse background and have little to no idea about what they are doing;
- Administrative services have a skewed perspective about what is important. They concentrate on bureaucratic meaningless reports and tasks that do not provide any value for the employees or the patients;
- The only goal outside of patient care: cost reduction;

Bottom line: if you are working with patients, you will like your job. Otherwise, and unless you have a sense of self importance about what you do, you will hate it because your ultimate goal is to cut cost while trying to not affect patient outcome (accent on *trying*) even if that's never phrased that way.
